Content: COLOMBO (News 1st):- The Department of Government Printing states that the process of printing the ballot papers for the Presidential election 2019 has ended. Government Printer Ganga Kalpani says that the ballot papers that have already been printed are now being inspected. She further said that the ballot papers will be handed over to the elections commission by next Tuesday (November 5), after they complete the inspection process. The total count of ballot papers that were printed for the Presidential election this year is over one billion.
